    installerScarcityPara: `Atlanta has roughly 3,600 active Georgia Residential Basic Contractor-licensed roofing contractors across the metro, with about 450-600 holding current factory-certified status on major composition brands. Post-storm surge events (2011, 2014, 2017 tornado outbreaks) brought out-of-state storm-chase crews; local pre-2018 reference-checking is critical. Atlanta Urban Design Commission (AUDC) jurisdictions narrow the qualified pool for landmarked work to 60-90 crews metro-wide, driving 10-16 week lead times on Inman Park, Grant Park, and Druid Hills historic projects.`,
    energyCreditsPara: `Atlanta homeowners layer Georgia Power Home Energy Improvement Program plus federal 25C credit (30% of cost up to $1,200 annually) on qualifying reroof scope. Georgia has a modest state income tax deduction for energy-efficiency improvements. Class 4 impact-rated assemblies return 10-20% insurance premium reductions. Federal 30% ITC applies to coordinated solar installations; Atlanta solar returns 9-13 year payback. Georgia Solar Access Law (O.C.G.A. §44-9-40) protects homeowner solar rights against HOA restrictions.`,
