  "atlanta-ga": `Atlanta reroof maintenance cycles: composition roof inspection every 3-5 years with algae-resistant granule assessment; non-AR composition requires cleaning or replacement as visible streaking appears. Gutter cleaning three times annually on tree-canopy properties in Druid Hills, Morningside, and Ansley Park due to heavy leaf and pollen fall. Termite infestation of wood fascia is a chronic Atlanta concern. Flashing and sealant refresh every 5-8 years due to humidity cycling. Post-storm inspection after tornado or hail events. Algae-resistant granule effectiveness typically degrades at year 10-15 requiring re-application or product replacement.`,
  "denver-co": `Denver reroof maintenance cycles: Class 4 impact-rated composition inspection every 2-3 years due to hail frequency; full post-hail event inspection within 30 days of every major storm. Synthetic underlayment inspection at year 15-20 to catch degradation before widespread failure. Gutter cleaning twice annually plus heated-cable system testing pre-winter. Ice-and-water-shield integrity assessment every 5-7 years. Flashing and sealant refresh every 5-7 years due to high-altitude UV and freeze-thaw cycling. Post-chinook-wind event inspection; chinook gusts can lift and damage composition.`,
  "seattle-wa": `Seattle reroof maintenance cycles: composition roof inspection every 3-5 years with moss and algae assessment; non-AR composition requires annual moss treatment from year 3 onward. Cedar shake requires cedar-specific stain or semi-transparent finish every 5-7 years to prevent moisture intrusion and biological degradation. Gutter cleaning three times annually on tree-canopy properties in Queen Anne, Ballard, and Wallingford due to heavy conifer debris. Zinc or copper ridge strip replacement every 15-20 years. Cascadia earthquake post-event inspection; seismic shaking can loosen fastener patterns.`,
  "austin-tx": `Austin reroof maintenance cycles: Class 4 impact-rated composition inspection every 2-4 years due to Hill Country hail exposure; full post-hail event inspection within 30 days. Flashing and sealant refresh every 5-7 years due to UV and humidity cycling. Gutter cleaning twice annually on tree-canopy properties in Hyde Park, Clarksville, and Travis Heights due to live-oak and pecan debris. Post-Uri 2021 thermal-shock inspection is ongoing concern on pre-Uri installations. Limestone-faced West Austin homes require specific cleaning protocols to avoid stone mortar damage during roof maintenance.`,
  "san-francisco-ca": `SF reroof maintenance cycles: composition roof inspection every 3-5 years with algae and moss assessment (microclimate-variable, aggressive in fog-belt Sunset and Richmond); tile-roof underlayment inspection every 10-15 years. Gutter cleaning three times annually on tree-canopy properties in Presidio Heights, Pacific Heights, and Noe Valley due to heavy eucalyptus and cypress debris. Post-atmospheric-river storm inspection baseline. Seismic inspection post-earthquake for fastener integrity. Victorian and Edwardian landmarked roofs require specialty restoration protocols with matching period materials.`,
  "las-vegas-nv": `Vegas reroof maintenance cycles: tile-roof underlayment inspection every 10-15 years to catch failure before monsoon water intrusion; composition roof flashing and sealant inspection every 2-4 years due to accelerated UV aging. Foam roof systems require 5-year elastomeric re-coat. Dust-storm debris removal from valleys and flashing annually. Monsoon pre-season (June) and post-monsoon (October) inspection baseline. UV-degraded sealants on south and west elevations typically require refresh every 5-8 years. HOA requires many master-planned-community maintenance protocols to preserve ARC-approved aesthetic.`,
  "philadelphia-pa": `Philadelphia reroof maintenance cycles: rowhouse flat-roof EPDM and modified bitumen require annual preventative-maintenance inspection to maintain 15-20 year warranty; parapet cap-flashing inspection critical because failure is the #1 Philly flat-roof failure mode. Pitched-roof Northwest Philly composition inspection every 3-5 years. Gutter cleaning twice annually on Germantown and Mount Airy tree-canopy properties. Rowhouse party-wall coordination with adjacent property owners on shared flashing. Chimney flashing and scupper drainage integrity annually on pre-1950 rowhouses.`,
  "miami-fl": `Miami reroof maintenance cycles: tile-roof underlayment inspection every 10-15 years to catch failure before hurricane-season water intrusion; NOA compliance verification annually on every installation. Flat-roof TPO and modified bitumen require annual preventative-maintenance inspection to maintain warranty. Hurricane-season pre-storm inspection (May) and post-storm inspection (November) baseline. Gutter and scupper integrity assessment annually in coastal-adjacent Coral Gables and Coconut Grove. Salt-air aluminum component replacement typically required every 10-15 years on coastal properties. Citizens Property Insurance wind-mitigation re-inspection every 5 years.`,
