  "san-diego-ca": `San Diego reroof maintenance cycles: tile-roof underlayment inspection every 10-15 years; composition roof flashing and sealant inspection every 3-5 years. Gutter cleaning twice annually on tree-canopy properties in Kensington, Bankers Hill, and South Park. Coastal-adjacent properties in La Jolla, Del Mar, and Encinitas require marine-grade fastener replacement every 10-12 years due to salt-air corrosion. WUI zone ember-resistant vent screen inspection annually. Santa Ana wind events trigger unscheduled inspection needs. Mills Act historic properties require specific preservation-grade maintenance protocols.`,
  "tampa-fl": `Tampa reroof maintenance cycles: tile-roof underlayment inspection every 10-15 years; composition roof inspection every 2-3 years due to UV and humidity aging. FPA compliance verification annually on coastal-adjacent installations. Hurricane-season pre-storm inspection (May) and post-storm inspection (November) baseline. Gutter and scupper integrity assessment annually in South Tampa, Davis Islands, and Westshore coastal-adjacent properties. Salt-air aluminum component replacement typically required every 10-15 years on Gulf-facing properties. Citizens Property Insurance wind-mitigation re-inspection every 5 years under OIR-B1-1802 form.`,
  "detroit-mi": `Detroit reroof maintenance cycles: pitched-roof composition inspection every 3-5 years with particular attention to ice-and-water-shield integrity at eaves; flat-roof EPDM and modified bitumen require annual preventative-maintenance inspection. Ice-dam damage assessment after every major winter storm event. Gutter cleaning three times annually on Rosedale Park, Sherwood Forest, and suburban tree-canopy properties. Slate roof maintenance on landmarked Boston-Edison and Indian Village homes involves individual slate replacement every 10-15 years. Chimney flashing in Detroit freeze-thaw climate typically requires repair every 10-15 years; Great Lakes salt-spray accelerates deterioration.`,
  "minneapolis-mn": `Minneapolis reroof maintenance cycles: pitched-roof composition inspection every 3-5 years with particular attention to 6-foot ice-and-water-shield integrity at eaves; Class 4 impact-rated composition post-hail event inspection within 30 days of major storms. Heated-cable system testing pre-winter and post-winter assessment. Gutter cleaning three times annually (late fall, mid-winter thaw, spring). Snow-retention system inspection at eaves on metal-roof installations to prevent dangerous avalanche events. Attic ventilation and R-49+ insulation assessment annually to prevent ice-dam formation at source. Chimney flashing in extreme freeze-thaw climate requires repair every 8-12 years.`,
